CALL FOR PAPERS

Workshop on Games, Dialogue and Interaction
 http://anr-prelude.fr
University of Paris =96 VIII
September 28/29, 2009


BACKGROUND

This workshop is to be held in the frame of the PRELUDE project
(funded by the French ANR =96 Agence Nationale pour la Recherche), which
is a joint project of four research teams : laboratoire =93Structures
Formelles de la Langue=94 (Paris VIII and CNRS), Institut de
math=E9matiques de Luminy (Aix-Marseille and CNRS), Laboratoire
d=92informatique de Bordeaux (=E9quipe Signes) (Bordeaux I, CNRS and
INRIA) and Laboratoire lorrain de recherches en informatique et
applications (LORIA, Nancy). It will be hosted by the CNRS center of
59 rue Pouchet, PARIS (17e).

AIMS AND SCOPE

=93PRELUDE=94 stands for =93Towards a Theoretical Pragmatic based on Ludics
and Continuations=94, that is to say that a particular emphasis has been
put during all these years on the use of new formal tools coming from
Theoretical Computer Science and Logic in order to give new
formulations for language phenomena pertaining to formal semantics
(logical forms), pragmatics (dialogue, presupposition) and even
argumentation (fallacies and stratagems).
As indicated by its title, this workshop will be devoted on all
aspects of the formal study of dialogue and interactions: syntax of
dialogue, semantic, pragmatic and philosophical aspects.

